    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1953-09-17T18:06:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1953-09-17T18:06:00-05:00" n="472"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d472">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">320/9–1653: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Embassy in the Republic of China</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d472fn1">Sent also to <gloss target="#t_USUN1">USUN</gloss>
                        (for the U.S. Delegation to the General Assembly) as telegram <gloss
                            target="#t_GADel1">Gadel</gloss> 6.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1953-09-17T19:06:00-04:00"
                            >September 17, 1953—7:06 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>228. Re <gloss target="#t_urtel1">urtel</gloss> 164 inform Foreign Minister it
                    would not be feasible delete phrase since <gloss target="#t_GA1">GA</gloss> has
                    already adopted resolution. You should also explain we expect 8th <gloss
                        target="#t_GA1">GA</gloss> to adjourn (and not recess) by end 1953. In this
                    event, deletion of phrase would have no practical effect.</p>
                <p>Credentials Committee already appointed by <persName corresp="#p_PEARSONLB1"
                        >Pearson</persName> as Acting President. Committee of nine has only three
                    Members (<gloss target="#t_UK1">UK</gloss>, <gloss target="#t_USSR1"
                        >USSR</gloss>, and Indonesia) which recognize Chinese Communist regime.
                    Furthermore, even if Chinese representation issue raised in Committee, we
                    believe latter could not consider it in view action already taken by
                    Assembly.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SMITHWB1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Smith</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
